      "url": "https://aisensy.com/case-studies/delhi-transport-corporation",
      "title": "Delhi Transport Corporation",
      "page_type": "blog",
      "summary": "Discover how Delhi Transport Corporation (DTC) streamlined bus ticket booking by leveraging WhatsApp's chatbot automation | AiSensy",
      "content": "Get Started for Free\nBook a Demo\nIndustry\nPublic Transportation\nHeadquarters\nIP Estate, New Delhi\nCompany Size\n27,000+ Employees\nServices\nAffordable and accessible public transportation\nComplex Ticketing Process\nTraditional ticket booking methods were tedious, requiring passengers to use confusing booking portals. Moreover, users faced the language barrier, finding it difficult to book bus tickets.\nLimited Accessibility\nMany commuters found it difficult to access ticket booking systems, especially for last-minute or on-the-go reservations. This led to DTC searching for one single platform, allowing users to book tickets with ease.\nOperational Inefficiency\nHandling a large volume of daily bookings manually or via traditional portals was time-consuming and inefficient. DTC was looking for a solution that could be automated and scalable.\nConvenient and User-Friendly\nWhatsApp is the one app that united all Indian users. WhatsApp has over 650 mn+ Indian users (2.7 Bn+ globally) across multiple age groups who are familiar with it's interface. WhatsApp provides a simple and user-friendly way for commuters to book tickets directly through an app they use every day.\nInstant Access\nPassengers could easily access ticket booking anytime, anywhere, without the need for physical ticket counters or going through complex digital portals.\nMultilingual Support\nBy enabling booking in\nboth Hindi and English\n, the service became more accessible to a diverse range of users across Delhi.\nBus Ticket booking begins with Chatbot automation\nThe entire conversational journey of the DTC bus ticket booking experience on WhatsApp is built using AiSensy's Chatbot Flow builder.\nA user simply needs to send a\n'\nhi\n' on Delhi Transport Corporation's WhatsApp number, \"+\n918744073223\n\" to begin the ticket booking process\nNext, the user picks their preferred language and selects the action they wish to achieve, i.e.\nBook Ticket\nThe straightforward conversational flow allows users to complete a ticket purchase in a few simple steps, significantly enhancing user engagement.\nUser selects their destination Bus stop via WhatsApp Webviews\nTo allow users to seamlessly select their destination station, we partnered with PeLocal who built the webviews for this ticketing process.\nWhatsApp webviews enabled users to open web browser within WhatsApp, allowing them to pick their stop easily in just a few taps.\nUser completes the payment directly within WhatsApp & receives QR Ticket\nOnce the user successfully picks their preferred destination, they receive a payment message on WhatsApp, prompting them to complete their ticket purchase.\nIf they've selected UPI, users can complete the payment conveniently natively within WhatsApp, skipping the process of going to a 3rd party payment app.\n14 Lakh+\nTickets Sold\nSince launch, over\n14 Lakh+ bus tickets\nhave been booked via WhatsApp.\nMultilingual\nChatbot\nUsers can book their bus ticket in the language they are most comfortable in i.e.\nHindi or English\n2x U",
