      "content": "Start for FREE\nBook a Demo\nSign Up for Integrately\nSign up for a free Integrately account. If you already have one, proceed to the next step.\nSign Up (FREE)\nChoose Your Apps\nIn Integrately's Dashboard, search for the apps you want to connect. Here, we'll connect Calendly with AiSensy.\nTip:\nFor AiSensy, search using keywords like \"WhatsApp\" or \"AiSensy.\"\nSelect Triggers & Actions\nDefine the purpose of the connection. For example, in Calendly, select triggers like \"Invitee Created\" or \"Invitee Canceled.\"\nNote:\nOnly one trigger can be used per WhatsApp API campaign.\nA WhatsApp message will be automated to the user upon activation of the trigger. When a trigger activates, it will initiate an action via AiSensy. i.e.\nSend a WhatsApp Template Message\n.\nAfter selecting the Trigger & Action, press \"\nGo\n\", to create your automation.\nGo to Integrations in Calendly\nNow, we need to copy the API Keys of both the Apps to integrate them.\nFirst, go to Calendly & reach the Integrations page. Then, scroll down & click on, \"\nAPI & Webhooks\n\".\nCopy Calendly's API Key\nIn the next screen, copy Calendly's API key.\nPaste the API Key in Integrately\nGo to Integrately's Dashboard & paste Calendly's API Key.\nClick \"Continue\" after you paste the API key.\nCopy Meet Key from Calendly\nOn the next screen, you'll be asked to send a test record in Calendly that will fire up when an \"Invitee is created\" (our trigger).\nYou can also make changes to the \"Meeting\" like adding questions, changing meeting duration etc.\nIn a fresh tab, open the link & schedule a test meet!\nHit \"Refresh Data\"\nBack in Integrately, hit \"\nRefresh Data\n\". It will appear as shown in the image.\nIf not, go back 👉 Schedule another meet 👉 Refresh Data.\nCopy AiSensy API Key\nNow, let's connect the API Key of AiSensy to connect Calendly & AiSensy.\nGo to AiSensy App 👉 Manage 👉 API Key 👉 Copy API Key\nPaste AiSensy API Key in Integrately\nPaste the AiSensy API Key by clicking \"Add Connection\" in Integrately.\nMap Attributes\nMap user data from Calendly to AiSensy. This includes details like name, mobile number, and country code.\nHere, add your Campaign name exactly as it shows on AiSensy Campaign Page.\nNote: If you haven't yet set an Active Campaign live in AiSensy, do it! This step is compulsory for the integration to work!\nHow to set API Campaigns in AiSensy\nAdd Tags & Attributes\nAdd tags and attributes in AiSensy to better organize your leads.\nIn this example, we segregate based on gender.\nThese tags will appear in the user's profile in AiSensy.\nHow to Create Tags and Attributes in AiSensy\nTest & Activate Automation\nOnce you've mapped all data, verify & hit \"\nTest & Activate\n\" to activate your automation.\nAutomation Activated Successfully🎉\nIf all steps were performed correctly, you'll see the screen shown in the image.\nThis means your automation is successfully activated. Whenever a user schedules a meeting, they will receive an automated notification with their name & time of the meeting.\nMessage received\nHere, you can ",
