      "summary": "Seamlessly connect your WooCommerce store with AiSensy and automate notifications for order, delivery, feedback & more on WhatsApp!",
      "content": "Start for FREE\nBook a Demo\nLearn More\nRecover Abandoned Carts\nAutomate personalized WhatsApp reminders to customers who left items in their cart to complete their purchase.\nOrder Confirmation & Updates\nProvide instant order confirmations, shipping updates, and delivery notifications via WhatsApp\nReduce RTO (Return to Origin)\nConfirm COD orders and cut down on returns with WhatsApp notifications.\nFeedback Collection & Reviews\nGather valuable insights to improve your products and services.\nTimely Reorder Reminders\nBoost repeat purchases by proactively reminding customers to restock their favorite products.\nPromotional Campaigns & Offers\nLaunch promotions, send offers, and drive engagement directly through WhatsApp.\nGenerate API Keys from your WooCommerce store\nThe first step to connect your WooCommerce store with AiSensy is generating secret API keys from your WooCommerce dashboard.\nFollow the steps mentioned in the below doc to generate these keys.\nGenerate WooCommerce Secret API Keys\nIn AiSensy Dashboard, go to Ecomm+\nGo to\nEcomm+.\nUnder WooCommerce click\nStore setup.\nLearn More\nEnter credentials of your WooCommerce Store\nNext, copy-paste your\nWooCommerce\nShop Name, Shop URL, Consumer Key & Consumer Secret Key\ngenerated through WooCommerce &\nclick\nConnect\n.\nKindly ensure that you enter the Shop name & shop URL in the below mentioned format only:\n✅\nWooCommerce Shop Name format:\nYour Shop Name (e.g. Flipkart)\n✅\nWooCommerce Shop URL format:\nhttps://yourshopname.com\n(e.g. https://flipkart.com)\nWooCommerce store is successfully connected\nIf the details you entered are correct, you'll see the WooCommerce store status as\nConnected.\nStart for FREE\nBook a Demo",
