      "content": "Start for FREE\nBook a Demo\nProfessional storefront\nOrganize up to 500 products with high-resolution photos, detailed descriptions, and up-to-date pricing.\nFaster orders\nCustomers select items and send them directly in the chat. No calls, no back-and-forth. The buying process is up to 3x faster.\nAI automation\nWith AiSensy, an AI agent answers catalog questions 24/7, qualifies leads, and completes orders automatically.\nScalability\nShow more items and handle more complex queries without the app's restrictions.\nAutomation\nIntegrate with CRM systems and automate everything from order confirmations to inventory updates.\nAdvanced Analytics\nGet detailed insights into customer behavior, helping you make informed decisions.\nCreate a AiSensy Account and Apply for Free WhatsApp Business API\nSign up at\nAiSensy.com\nand complete your profile.\nIn your AiSensy dashboard apply for\nWhatsApp Business API\nand and submit your business details.\nCreate an Account\nUnlock Flow Builder\nAccess the Flow Builder in the AiSensy app under \"Flows.\" Purchase the add-on.\nPricing Page\nConnect Your Facebook Business Account\nIn \"Flows,\" navigate to \"Connect Catalog\" and link your Facebook Business account. Ensure your catalog is already created in Facebook.\nLearn More\nLink Your Catalog to WhatsApp\nGo to \"Manage Catalog\" in Flows and connect the Facebook catalog you wish to use.\nGo to Product & edit the listed products (Optional)\nNext, go to the\nProducts\nsection, which includes all the products listed in your Shopify account.\nIf you want, you can edit these products by clicking the\npencil\nicon.\nClicking the pencil icon will take you to Shopify from where you'll be able to edit these products.\nCreate a New Flow\nNow, go to\nFlow Builder\nand click\nCreate Flow\nto create the flow for your WhatsApp Catalog.\nSet Up Your Trigger — Keywords or AI\nOnce the Flow Builder opens, you need to define what triggers your Catalog flow.\nOption 1 — Keyword Trigger (standard):\nAdd keywords like\nShop, Products, Hi\nthat customers commonly send. Whenever a user sends a matching keyword to your WhatsApp number, the catalog flow triggers automatically.\nOption 2 — AI Agent Trigger (recommended):\nWith AiSensy's\nAI Agents\n, your catalog can be triggered by\nany\ncustomer message — no exact keyword match needed. The AI understands intent, so even a message like \"What do you sell?\" or \"Show me your collection\" will open your catalog automatically.\nSet up an AI Agent\nSave and Activate Your Flow\nOnce satisfied with your flow, click\n\"Save\"\nand enable it to make your catalog live on WhatsApp.\nFor a detailed guide, check our tutorial:\nLearn More\nBuild Your AI Agent\nUnlock Flow Builder\nExcellent\n4.4\nour of\n5\nbased on\n660 reviews\nWhat is better: to create a WhatsApp Catalog via the WhatsApp Business App or API?\nCreating a catalog via the WhatsApp Business App is simpler and faster, ideal for small businesses. However, using the API through platforms like AiSensy is better for businesses that need scalability, automation, and ",
